file.name: openapi.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: Tradier API
  version: v1
servers:
- description: Tradier Sandbox
  url: https://sandbox.tradier.com/v1
security:
- BearerAuth: []
paths:
  /markets/quotes:
    get:
      description: |
        Get a list of symbols using a keyword lookup on the symbols description. Results are in descending order by average volume of the security. This can be used for simple search functions.
      parameters:
      - explode: false
        in: query
        name: symbols
        required: true
        schema:
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/symbol'
          type: array
        style: simple
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: greeks
        required: false
        schema:
          type: boolean
        style: form
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/quotes'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
    post:
      description: |
        Get a list of symbols using a keyword lookup on the symbols description. Results are in descending order by average volume of the security. This can be used for simple search functions.
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/x-www-form-urlencoded:
            schema:
              properties:
                symbols:
                  items:
                    $ref: '#/components/schemas/symbol'
                  type: array
                greeks:
                  default: false
                  type: boolean
              required:
              - symbols
        required: true
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/quotes'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /markets/options/chains:
    get:
      description: |
        Get all quotes in an option chain. Greek and IV data is included courtesy of ORATS. Please check out their APIs for more in-depth options data.
      parameters:
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: symbol
        required: true
        schema:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/symbol'
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: expiration
        required: true
        schema:
          format: date
          type: string
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: greeks
        required: false
        schema:
          type: boolean
        style: form
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_2XX'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /markets/options/expirations:
    get:
      description: |
        Get expiration dates for a particular underlying.

        Note that some underlying securities use a different symbol for their weekly options (RUT/RUTW, SPX/SPXW). To make sure you see all expirations, make sure to send the includeAllRoots parameter. This will also ensure any unique options due to corporate actions (AAPL1) are returned.
      parameters:
      - description: Underlying symbol of the chain
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: symbol
        required: true
        schema:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/symbol'
        style: form
      - description: Send expirations related to all option roots
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: includeAllRoots
        required: false
        schema:
          default: false
          type: boolean
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: strikes
        required: false
        schema:
          default: false
          type: boolean
        style: form
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_2XX_1'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /markets/options/strikes:
    get:
      description: |
        Get an options strike prices for a specified expiration date.
      parameters:
      - description: Underlying symbol of the chain
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: symbol
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: expiration
        required: false
        schema:
          format: date
          type: string
        style: form
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_2XX_2'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /markets/options/lookup:
    get:
      description: |
        Get all options symbols for the given underlying. This will include additional option roots (ex. SPXW, RUTW) if applicable.
      parameters:
      - description: Underlying symbol of the chain
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: underlying
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        style: form
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_2XX_3'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /user/profile:
    get:
      description: |
        The user’s profile contains information pertaining to the user and his/her accounts. In addition to listing all the accounts a user has, this call should be used to create a personalized experience for your customers (i.e. displaying their name when they log in).
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/profile'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /markets/events/session:
    post:
      description: |
        Create a streaming session for use with the Tradier Streaming API. This session can be used with the streaming endpoints to obtain updates to the market as they happen.
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_2XX_4'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
  /markets/history:
    get:
      description: |
        Get historical pricing for a security. This data will usually cover the entire lifetime of the company if sending reasonable start/end times. You can fetch historical pricing for options by passing the OCC option symbol (ex. AAPL220617C00270000) as the symbol.
      parameters:
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: symbol
        required: true
        schema:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/symbol'
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: interval
        required: false
        schema:
          enum:
          - daily
          - weekly
          - monthly
          type: string
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: start
        required: false
        schema:
          format: date
          type: string
        style: form
      - explode: true
        in: query
        name: end
        required: false
        schema:
          format: date
          type: string
        style: form
      responses:
        "2XX":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_2XX_5'
          description: OK
      security:
      - BearerAuth: []
